issues.title: django-ticketoffice provides web API to manage ticket

milestone.title: Later
milestone.description: Features/bugfixes that we plan to implement, whenever we can. No urge, not a priority.

issues.body:
See docs/about/vision.
As software built on top of Django, it should not be over-complicated for django-ticketoffice to provide a web API to manage tickets and authenticate.
Of course, such a feature must be configurable (at least, developers must be able to enable/disable it). Maybe a set of generic views.

If the implementation requires too much dependencies (restframework or things like that), wonder about packaging this feature as a standalone project: when developers just want the "client" features of django-ticketoffice, do they want to download a bunch of server-related dependencies?

milestone.title: Maybe, one of these days

milestone.title: Later
milestone.description: Features/bugfixes that we plan to implement, whenever we can. No urge, not a priority.

issues.body:
Primary use case is to provide unlimited usage.
Could be implemented with a simple boolean ("unlimited_usage" or something like that).
Could also be implemented with a counter which is decremented each time the ticket is used. A "-1" value would mean "unlimited_usage".

commit.message: In invitation_required decorator, UUID value submitted by user gets validated via TicketAuthenticationForm. Closes #4.
Refs #4 - In TicketAuthenticationForm, validate UUID format.
Refs #4 - Adds UUID bad format test when retrieve ticket form session value.
Refs #4 - Adds missing UUID format check.
Refs #4 - Filters Tickets objects with real UUID object to ensure good python/db compliance.
Fixed latex options for documentation. Fixes documentation build on readthedocs.org. Closes #19.
Refs #19 - Project slug in docs/conf.py was '-', so pdflatex thought it was a command-line option.
Restored the demo project. Even empty, it is actually used to run the tests.
Store ticket UUID as string, with hyphens, in session. Closes #14.
Refs #14 - 'hyphenate' option is available in django-uuidfield>=0.5
Refs #14 - Make sure string representation of UUID contains hyphens. Added tests around ticket UUID storage in session.
Refs #14 - Casts uuid to store in session to ensure good serialization.
Updates Django version according current project achievement.
Added support for Django 1.6: updated usage of Django's password hashers. Closes #10.
Using tox to run the tests. Travis runs tox. Closes #12.
Merged branch 12-tox: using Tox to run the tests with both Django 1.5 and 1.6.
Introduced Tox, removed Buildout. Removed root package's API, because it was causing weird import errors.
Refs #10 - Updates tests according django 1.5 and 1.6 behaviours.
Refs #10 - Replaces UNUSABLE_PASSWORD that does not exist in django 1.6 with make_password that works for both of 1.5 and 1.6 versions.
Refs #11 - Removes too restrictive versions requirements for pip and setuptools.
Refs #11 - Fixes download 404 when installing due to index and allow-hosts limitation.

Merge pull request #9 from novapost/6-class-based-invitation-required

Closes #6 - Class-based @invitation_required
Refs #6 - In invitation_required decorator, restored redirection which hides credentials.
Refs #6 - Fixed TicketAuthenticationForm's initialization in invitation_required.get_ticket().
Refs #6 - Added decorators and exceptions to the API.

Refs #6 - Moved Ticket instance checks from TicketAuthenticationForm to invitation_required.get_ticket for smarter error handling (hard to get details about the validation errors if not form.is_valid()).
Refs #6 - Replaced some invitation_required options (forbidden, unauthorized and login) by internal (overridable) methods.
Refs #6 - Using class-based implementation for invitation_required decorator.
Using crate.io as index-url in virtualenv.

Merge pull request #3 from novapost/2-uuid-with-dashes

Closes #2 - Support UUID with dashes in @invitation_required decorator.
Refs #2 - Support UUID with dashes in @invitation_required decorator.
Exposed API (starting with Ticket model) in django_ticketoffice module.
Exposed API (starting with Ticket model) in django_ticketoffice module.
Initialized project with 'Ticket' model and 'invitation_required' decorator.

issue_comments.body: See also https://github.com/dcramer/django-uuidfield/pull/21

C'est ce que j'allais dire il vaudrait mieux faire

``` python
    try:
        data['uuid'] = str(UUID(data['uuid'])).replace('-', '')
    except ValueError:
        data['uuid'] = ''
```

> `uuid = str(UUID(data['uuid'])).replace('-', '')`

`data['uuid']` is an unicode (from `request.GET`), not a `uuid.UUID`, so `data['uuid'].replace('-', '')` is ok, isn't it?
It doesn't validate that the unicode string is a valid uuid.

> It doesn't validate that the unicode string is a valid uuid.

You are right. Created #4 for that purpose.
https://github.com/progrium/pyjwt
Note: the usage log (datetime) is still useful.
Wontfix. We'd better remove buildout and use tox.
Especially because you are asking version upgrade: tox will check backward compatibility, whereas current development environment based on buildout can't do that.
We need it to trigger tests on travis for current pull request https://github.com/novapost/django-ticketoffice/pull/10
Note: I'll try to integrate with #10 and, if it works, perhaps merge them together.
@toopy: are my updates ok for you? Notice I added `hyphenate=True` to UUIDField.

@toopy: I moved validation code from `invitation_required.get_ticket_from_credentials` to `TicketAuthenticationForm`.

And fixed some typos.

\o/

commit_comments.body:
You can even remove the version number, i.e. `s/Django<1.7/Django/`.
I added the limitation as part of #13, where I wanted to make sure Django 1.5 was used... But then in #10 you added support for Django 1.6, so it is ok to remove the version limit.
